Johannesburg A woman had a lucky escape and sustained only moderate injuries when she was struck by lightning in Carletonville, west of Johannesburg on Friday, ER24 paramedics said. &quot;The woman, believed to be in her 30s, was found seated in a passage at a business. Upon assessment it was found that she sustained moderate injuries. She was treated and transported to hospital for further medical care,&quot; said ER24 spokesperson Chitra Bodasing Harduth. African News Agency